= Reichstag Reconvenes

The Reichstag has reconvened for the first time since the election, with a significantly larger contingent of <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> members now present. The immediate issue at hand is the election of the President of the Reichstag. While the position has traditionally been a procedural one, it has taken on heightened importance under Papen's presidential government, given the President's authority to influence the agenda and adjourn sessions.

By long-standing custom, the role is granted to the largest parliamentary delegation. That delegation is now the <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span>. The <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> holds the balance of power. Will they uphold tradition and hand a key parliamentary post to an openly anti-constitutional party?

