With negotiations between the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> and the <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> underway, previously hostile relations have thawed enough for the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> to support Hermann Göring’s election as President of the Reichstag. The <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> delegation’s newfound decorum convinced many that the party had turned over a new leaf.

In line with a promise made to the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span>, the Reichstag has adjourned for two more weeks to allow coalition talks to take place. Yet unease is growing within the <span style="color: #000000;">Center Party</span> at the possibility of a <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span> chancellorship, and they may soon walk away from the table.

